# Agent skills

## Committed project skills (repo root)

These live under **`.cursor/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`** and apply to this codebase: e.g. **payment-plugin**, **shadcn**, **frontend-design**, **three-js**, **migrate-prisma-v7**, **r3f-fundamentals**. **`.claude/skills/<name>`** symlinks into **`.cursor/skills/<name>`**. If the user’s task matches one of these, **read `SKILL.md` first**.

## Optional user skills (`~/.agents/skills`)

Supplemental skills (TDD, PRDs, Stripe docs helpers, etc.) may exist only on the developer’s machine under **`~/.agents/skills/<name>/`**. The repo can expose them as **`web/.agents/skills-global`** after **`cd web && bun run link:agents-skills`** (gitignored symlink). If the task matches a skill name present there, **read `SKILL.md`** before improvising.

**Paths (pick one):**

- **`.cursor/skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`** — committed in repo
- **`~/.agents/skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`**
- **`web/.agents/skills-global/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`** — after running the link script from `web/`

## Known optional skills (examples)

When linked from `~/.agents/skills/`, examples include `stripe`, `tdd`, `find-skills`, `write-a-prd`, `prd-to-plan`, `design-an-interface`, `improve-codebase-architecture`, `triage-issue`, `setup-pre-commit`, and others present on disk.

## How to load

Use the Read tool on the concrete **`SKILL.md`** path. Follow that skill’s instructions for the rest of the task.
